review_blob: Nice vanilla and licorice nose, but overwhelming alcohol backbone made it hard for these flavors to come forward.  Needs more chewable malt characterisitcs.

A staple at most common denominator beer houses in Seattle.  Nice citrus zest for a Pale. Delivery is heavy in body, but light in taste.  Looking for more crisp malt and candy in the middle.  Finishes with a nice floral assortment.
Bold hop delivery on a scale rarely equaled anywhere else.  Pungent mossy taste with notes of pine, bark, and sour orange zest.  Finishes with a pleasing dance of the senses.

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: Pours a hazy shade of amber red.  Big grass, big citrus, with a candy middle and sweet floral finish.  All flavor is delivered in a big way but not overpowering, which makes for a very smooth and balanced DIPA.  A rare accomplishment for sure.
beer_name: Hair of the Dog Blue Dot Double IPA

review_blob: Smokey malts with hints of mossy earth, toffee, burnt vanilla cream, and a prolonged pungent finish.  I thought Boundary Bay had the corner on Scotch Ale, but no longer.
beer_name: Silver City Fat Woody Scotch Ale

review_blob: Displays some honey and vanilla upfront with a light trail of tangy orange and pungent earth.  Fades too quickly with a watered finale.
Big Northwest hops delivered up front and en masse.  Very buttery finish, an leaves with an earthy oil slick on the palate.
beer_name: Silver City Whoop Pass Double IPA

review_blob: Fishing for Coho on Thorne Island in Alaska (pop. 115) and miraculously the general store had a healthy stock of Maximus to go with your typical macro sewer water.  Now I know why.  Paired with a fresh catch of Silver Salmon, the bitter fruits reveal themselves nicely with a dry hoppy finish.
Suprisingly nice flavors with a malty backbone.  Scarlet and Copper tweener.
Love how this beer lingers with hints of citrus and huge malty roasts.  Paired with clams and this kid has reached total consciousness.
beer_name: Avery The Maharaja Imperial India Pale Ale
